nk\": 0.0009613909096332929, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 364, \"end\": 371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9988290579336139, \"rank\": 0.0011720357796304514, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her 800m silver medal\", \"from\": 244, \"to\": 265}, {\"ngram\": \"Tokyo\", \"from\": 269, \"to\": 274}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 296, \"to\": 300}, {\"ngram\": \"the admiration\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 360}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, for her exploits, Hodgkinson has been billed as the bonafide frontrunner to land the award - last won by Lionesses heroine Mary Earps in 2023 and her team-mate Beth Mead the year prior - ahead of fellow favourite darts phenom Luke Littler.\", \"from\": 378, \"to\": 622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 401, \"end\": 411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.752573988136437, \"rank\": 0.3287730053974598, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 506, \"end\": 516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Earps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mary Earps\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Earps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Earps\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her exploits\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 399}, {\"ngram\": \"the bonafide frontrunner\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 455}, {\"ngram\": \"the award\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 473}, {\"ngram\": \"the year prior - ahead\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 575}, {\"ngram\": \"fellow favourite darts\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 601}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hodgkinson may not just be rewarded with the trophy should she win on Tuesday (17 December) evening, either.\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 624, \"end\": 634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 0.752573988136437, \"rank\": 0.3287730053974598, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Hodgkinson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the trophy\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 675}, {\"ngram\": \"Tuesday\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 701}, {\"ngram\": \"evening\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A sports finance expert predicts that she will rake in a whopping \\u00a31million per year until the next Olympic Games in 2028 on the back of her anticipated SPOTY success.\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 886, \"end\": 891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sports_Personality_of_the_Year\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"SPOTY\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sports_Personality_of_the_Year\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sports_Personality_of_the_Year\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A sports finance expert\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 756}, {\"ngram\": \"year\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 817}, {\"ngram\": \"the next Olympic Games\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 846}, {\"ngram\": \"the back\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 866}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr Rob Wilson, speaking over the summer after Hodgkinson's medal win, exclusively toldinvestment platform Saxo: \\\"Keely is already becoming one of the most recognisable faces for UK athletics.\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 1093, \"entities\": [